# Testing and Debugging

## Test Environment

All tests use `TempDir` for isolation. `KnowledgeGraph::new(temp_dir.path())`
creates `<temp_dir>/knowledge.db` automatically. No `env.sh`, no model downloads,
no server needed.

Bind the `TempDir` to a named variable (`_tmp`), not `_` — `TempDir` deletes its
directory on drop. Discarding to `_` can drop before the test body runs.

---

## Running Tests

```bash
cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1                             # All tests — always single-threaded
cargo test --workspace storage -- --test-threads=1                     # Module-specific
cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1 --nocapture                 # With stdout
RUST_LOG=debug cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1 --nocapture  # With debug logging
cargo test --workspace test_name -- --exact --test-threads=1           # Single test by name
```

**Always pass `--test-threads=1`.** Integration tests share GPU/NPU hardware on
a live Lemonade Server and fail intermittently when run in parallel. Unit tests
pass with no external service; integration tests skip automatically when no
server is reachable.

---

## Mock providers

`MockEmbeddingProvider` and `MockTranscriptionProvider` are deterministic
in-memory impls — mock vectors vary by text length, mock transcripts echo the
filename. Copy the pattern when you need a provider in a unit test without a
live server.

Live references to copy from:
- `src/search/mod.rs` (`tests::MockEmbeddingProvider`)
- `src/queue/dispatch.rs` (`tests::MockEmbeddingProvider`, `MockTranscriptionProvider`)
- `src/ingest/embedding.rs` (`tests::MockEmbeddingProvider`)

Each test module defines its own mock rather than sharing one — small on-purpose
duplication, because different tests need slightly different vector shapes, and
a shared mock in a test utility crate would drag `u-forge-core` into a cyclical
test-only dependency.

> **There is no FastEmbed / local fallback.** FastEmbed and ONNX Runtime have
> been removed. Do not reference `FastEmbedProvider`, `try_new_local_default`,
> or `FASTEMBED_CACHE_PATH` — they no longer exist.

