## Audio test helper: `make_silence_wav`

Lives in `src/ai/transcription.rs` inside the `tests` module (`pub(crate)`).
Builds a valid mono 16-bit 16 kHz PCM WAV entirely in memory — no binary
fixtures. Copy the pattern when a test needs real audio bytes.

Silence input produces hallucinated transcripts by design — whisper-family
models hallucinate on silence. For tests that assert on content, use real
speech audio. For smoke tests of the transcribe path, only check `result.is_ok()`.

