## Lemonade integration tests — skip guard

Use the `require_integration_url!()` macro from `crate::test_helpers`. It probes
the live server and skips the test silently when none is reachable. Resolution
order:

1. `http://localhost:13305/api/v1` — probed via `GET /api/v1/health` (2 s timeout)
2. `http://127.0.0.1:13305/api/v1` — explicit IPv4 loopback
3. `LEMONADE_URL` env var — accepted as-is, no liveness check

Control variable:
- `UFORGE_INTEGRATION_TESTS=require` — panic instead of skip (CI enforcement)
- `UFORGE_INTEGRATION_TESTS=skip` — force-skip even when a server is present

Under the hood, `test_helpers::integration_test_url()` delegates to the
production `crate::lemonade::resolve_lemonade_url()` for the default (unset)
case — so tests and the app follow the same discovery logic.

---

## What each storage layer test must cover

- `upsert_node` — updating must not wipe edges/chunks (`ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE`)
- `delete_node` — verify `ON DELETE CASCADE` removes edges and chunks
- `search_chunks_fts` — insert a chunk, then query by keyword
- `query_subgraph` — verify BFS hop depth and edge deduplication

FTS5 query syntax supported: phrase (`"foo bar"`), prefix (`foo*`), boolean
(`foo AND bar`, `foo OR bar`, `foo NOT bar`), column filters.

