## Debugging

### Log levels

```bash
RUST_LOG=trace                                       # Everything
RUST_LOG=debug                                       # Development detail
RUST_LOG=info                                        # Normal operation
RUST_LOG=u_forge_core::graph::storage=debug          # Single module
RUST_LOG=u_forge_core::ingest=warn                   # Suppress noisy modules
```

### Common issues

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `openssl-sys` compile error | Missing system OpenSSL headers | `apt install pkg-config libssl-dev` (Ubuntu) |
| `Lemonade Server not available` | Server not running | `lemonade-server serve` — `localhost:13305` is auto-discovered |
| Transcription returns immediate error | Model not pulled or server can't open audio | `lemonade-server pull whisper-v3-turbo-FLM`; verify audio bytes are non-empty |
| Transcription test passes but text is noise | Silence input hallucinations are normal | Use real speech for content assertions; only check `result.is_ok()` for silence |
| FTS5 search returns nothing | Chunk not yet added for the object | Call `add_text_chunk` before `search_chunks_fts` |
| `database is locked` | Two processes sharing the same `knowledge.db` | Ensure only one writer at a time |
| Import creates 0 edges | Node names in edges don't match node names exactly | Check spelling; `resolve_node_id` does exact-match lookup |
| Schema validation fails on known type | Schema not loaded before validation | Call `SchemaIngestion::load_schemas_from_directory` and `save_schema` first |
| `cannot borrow … as mutable` in test | `TempDir` dropped too early | Bind `_tmp` to a named variable, not `_` |

---

## CI Commands

```bash
cargo fmt --check
cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings
cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1
cargo doc --no-deps --workspace
```

No `source env.sh` required. No model downloads. All commands work offline.
Integration tests auto-skip when no Lemonade Server is reachable — set
`UFORGE_INTEGRATION_TESTS=require` in CI to enforce them.
